<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Hangard Construction collects, uses and protects your personal data under UK GDPR, and your rights as a data subject."
  updated="June 2026"
>
  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Hangard Construction</strong> ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses and protects your personal information when you contact us or use our website, in accordance with the UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018. We are the data controller for the information you provide.</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>Hangard Construction is a construction and renovation firm based at 3 Anderson Close, Harefield, Uxbridge UB9 6HF. You can contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@hg-construction.co.uk">hello@hg-construction.co.uk</a> or on <a href="tel:+447734903439">07734 903439</a> about anything in this policy, including a request to exercise your data rights.</p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We only collect what we need to respond to you and carry out work:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Information you give us</strong> — when you complete our enquiry form, email or call us: your name, email address, phone number, postcode or area, and the details of your project or message.</li>
    <li><strong>Information collected automatically</strong> — our hosting provider keeps basic, security-related server logs (such as IP address and browser type). We do not currently run analytics or advertising tracking on this site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your information, and our lawful basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your enquiry, arrange a site survey and prepare a quote — on the basis of taking steps at your request before entering into a contract, and our <em>legitimate interest</em> in answering enquiries.</li>
    <li>To deliver and manage any work you engage us for — on the basis of performing our contract with you.</li>
    <li>To keep proper business, accounting and warranty records — on the basis of our legal obligations and legitimate interests.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not send marketing unless you have asked us to, and you can opt out at any time.</p>

  <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share it where necessary with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>trusted subcontractors and suppliers, only as needed to quote for or carry out your project;</li>
    <li>service providers who help us run the business (for example our website hosting and email providers), who act on our instructions;</li>
    <li>professional advisers, or where we are required to by law.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
  <p>We keep enquiry details only as long as needed to deal with your enquiry and a reasonable period afterwards. Where we carry out work for you, we keep project, financial and warranty records for as long as required for legal, tax and guarantee purposes (generally up to six years, or longer where a guarantee applies).</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under UK data protection law you have the right to access your information; to have it corrected or erased; to restrict or object to its use; to data portability; and, where we rely on consent, to withdraw it. To exercise any of these, contact us using the details above. We will respond within the time limits the law allows.</p>
  <p>If you are unhappy with how we have handled your data, you can complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" rel="nofollow">ico.org.uk</a>, although we would welcome the chance to put things right first.</p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to keep your information secure and to prevent unauthorised access, loss or misuse.</p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>For information about cookies and similar technologies, please see our <a href="/cookies">Cookies Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Other websites</h2>
  <p>Our site may link to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their content or privacy practices, and we encourage you to read their policies.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on this page, with the "last updated" date shown above.</p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>For any privacy question or request, email <a href="mailto:hello@hg-construction.co.uk">hello@hg-construction.co.uk</a> or call <a href="tel:+447734903439">07734 903439</a>.</p>
</LegalPage>
